Definition.Description:
This example demonstrates how to use multi-tasking in a real-time sequence.
The real-time sequence simulates two engine warmup phases. The first warmup phase sets the desired RPM to 2500 and waits for 25 seconds. The second warmup phase sets the desired RPM to 8000 and it also waits for 25 seconds before the engine turns off.
During both warmup phases, a parallel task monitors the engine temperature so that the engine does not overheat. As soon as the engine temperature rises above a certain value, the currently-active warmup phase stops and the engine shuts down.
In addition to the Engine Demo Advanced example, this real-time sequence updates the return value depending on the outcome of the warmup phases. If the engine shuts down due to an over-temperature problem, the return value is false.
Practice using the 'Stop Execution on Fail' option. If this parameter is not checked, the execution of the project will not stop even if a return value does not meet the configured conditions. If this parameter is checked, the execution of the project stops immediately.
